On 20.10.1844 the part in Northamptonshire  became part of Bedfordshire, so that thereafter Farndish was 
    entirely in Bedfordshire. 
    Abolished 25.3.1884 and added to the parish of Podington.
Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of Wellingborough.
Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of Newton Bromswold.

    area. See also Table 2, note (e).
